      • loadBytes

        DataBlockResult<byte[]> loadBytes(int offset)
                                  throws JasDBStorageException
        Load bytes from the datablock, providing an offset from the start of the block. If the offset exceeds the block size it will start loading from the block chain.
        Parameters:
        offset - The offset to start loading the data from
        Returns:
        The bytes loaded fully into memory
        Throws:
        JasDBStorageException - If unable to load the bytes from the block
